    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Pale Maw Acolytes are cultists of Grafvitnir's corruption network, trained to channel necrotic and corruption energies through their bodies. Their pale, mottled skin and hollow eyes mark them as partially consumed by the Pale Maw—the name given to the corruption that spreads through contact with Grafvitnir's agents. They move with unnerving silence and strike without warning, vanishing into shadows between blows.</p>",
      "director": "<p>Pale Maw Acolytes work best in pairs—as deployed in the Beat 7 failure combat. Use Shadow Fade to reposition after Corruption Lash, staying mobile and forcing the PCs to track multiple threats. The Acolytes are fragile; use the Landvaettr as cover. Pale Maw Fervor triggers on each enemy kill, making each Acolyte more dangerous as the fight progresses. Prioritise isolated PCs or anyone distracted by the Landvaettr.</p>",
